<PolicyPage ID="x63643" Name="Off-Track Single Student Policy" Layout="general_Policy.xsl"><Title type="string" label="Policy Title" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="true">Off-Track Single Student Policy</Title><Abstract type="string" label="Policy Abstract" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="true">This document outlines the basic requirements of Approved Housing. This document does not necessarily represent all the requirements. Please contact Jon Phister to learn more.</Abstract><Date type="date" label="Revision Date" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="true" display="localdateshort" UTC="true">20110721T06:00:00</Date><BodyCopy type="dhtml" label="Policy" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false"><![CDATA[<hr />
<p>Current matriculating single students who are off-track and continue to live in the immediate Rexburg area are required to live in BYU-Idaho approved, single-student housing as a condition of their continued enrollment.</p>
<p>BYU-Idaho single students continuing their education at BYU-Idaho are required to live in approved housing unless an exception has been granted. Please<a href="x21792.xml"> contact the Housing &amp; Student Living Office</a> if you have any questions or concerns.</p>
